# Backend Changes Report

This document detail all backend modifications and additions implemented during this integration session.

## 1. Analytics Module

### [AnalyticsController](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/analytics/analytics.controller.ts)
- **[NEW] Endpoint `GET admin/summary`**: 
    - Consolidates platform-wide metrics (total businesses, customers, visits).
    - Returns data for growth trends (12 months), sector distribution, and recent security alerts.
    - Restricted to the `ADMIN` role.
- **[DELETE] Endpoint `GET admin/loyalty/stats`**: 
    - Removed the old mock endpoint in favor of the new consolidated summary.

### [AnalyticsService](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/analytics/analytics.service.ts)
- **[NEW] [getAdminSummary()](file:///C:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/analytics/analytics.service.ts#226-306)**:
    - **Platform Stats**: Direct count queries on [Business](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/businesses/entities/business.entity.ts#29-137), [User](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/VemTap/app/admin/users/page.tsx#8-19) (filtered by CUSTOMER), and [Visit](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/visitors/entities/visit.entity.ts#8-49) repositories.
    - **Growth Trend**: Implemented a TypeORM `QueryBuilder` using `TO_CHAR` for PostgreSQL to aggregate visits by month over the last fiscal year.
    - **Sector Split**: Aggregation by `business.category` with percentage calculation.
    - **Security Alerts (Security Pulse)**: 
    - Implemented real-time tracking of `suspended` businesses.
    - Dynamically retrieves the 3 most recently suspended accounts with their suspension reasons.
    - Provides a "Security Alert" if any risks are found, or a "System Clean" status if none.
    - This data feeds the "Security Pulse" section on both Analytics and Loyalty pages.

---

## 2. Support Module

### [SupportController](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.controller.ts)
- **[NEW] Endpoint `GET admin/tickets`**: Lists all platform tickets for administrative review.
- **[NEW] Endpoint `GET admin/tickets/:id`**: Provides full conversation history for any ticket (bypasses user-ownership checks).
- **[NEW] Endpoint `POST admin/tickets/:id/status`**: Allows admins to update ticket status (Resolve/Close).
- **[NEW] Endpoint `POST admin/tickets/:id/message`**: Allows agents/admins to reply to any customer ticket.

### [SupportService](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.service.ts)
- **[NEW] [findAllAdmin()](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.service.ts#71-77)**: Returns all tickets with user relations, ordered by creation date.
- **[NEW] [findOneAdmin(id)](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.service.ts#78-86)**: Fetches a specific ticket with all messages and participant info.
- **[NEW] [updateStatus(id, status)](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.service.ts#87-94)**: Direct state management for ticket lifecycles.
- **[NEW] [addAdminMessage(...)](file:///c:/Users/user/Desktop/mcom%20works/Vemtap/apps/backend/src/modules/support/support.controller.ts#89-92)**: 
    - Injects an agent response into the ticket thread.
    - Automatically transitions `Open` tickets to `In Progress` when an agent first replies.

---

## Technical Summary
- **Database**: PostgreSQL.
- **ORM**: TypeORM (QueryBuilder utilized for complex aggregations).
- **Security**: All new admin endpoints are protected by `JwtAuthGuard` and `RolesGuard(UserRole.ADMIN)`.
